with <CLASS SOCIALRANK="NOBILITY">upper-class</CLASS> connections.hfdjfdjh </P></CULTURALFORMATION></DIV1><DIV1><HEADING>Mother</HEADING><FAMILY><P>Her mother is oficially styled <NAME STANDARD="Mary Keen">Lady Priscilla Mary Rose Keen</NAME>, reflecting her birth as the daughter of an earl. She is a graduate of <ORGNAME STANDARD="Lady Margaret Hall, Oxford Umiversity">Lady Margaret Hall, Oxord</ORGNAME>. She is generally known as Mary Keen, and by the world of gardening as a <JOB>garden designer</JOB> and <JOB>writer</JOB>, a regular contributor to the <TITLE TITLETYPE="JOURNAL">Daily Telegraph</TITLE> which on 30 January 2015 published her article <TITLE TITLETYPE="ANALYTIC">Which famous women live on in plant names?</TITLE><BIBCITS><BIBCIT PLACEHOLDER="Keen" REF="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/orlando%3A81f86735-1592-4795-9816-740a7a98325c"/><BIBCIT PLACEHOLDER="The Peerage, under Lady Priscilla Mary Rose Curzon" REF="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/orlando%3Af8b72982-0a54-4329-bcbe-03377f3e18db"/></BIBCITS> </P><HEADING>Father</HEADING></FAMILY><FAMILY><P>AO's father, <NAME>Charles William Lyle Keen</NAME>, is a retired <JOB>army officer</JOB> and <JOB REG="bank director">director of a local bank</JOB>.<BIBCITS/> </P><HEADING>Siblings</HEADING></FAMILY><FAMILY><P>One of AO's two elder sisters, <NAME>Laura Beatty</NAME>, is also having some success as a <JOB>writer</JOB>.</P><P>Their younger brother, <NAME>Will Keen</NAME>, is an <JOB>actor</JOB>.</P><P>AO later recalled: <QUOTE DIRECT="Y">We were very close: a gang of children in an aesthetically amazing, protected environment.</QUOTE><BIBCITS/> </P></FAMILY></DIV1><DIV1><LOCATION>AO spent most of her childhood at her parents' home, <PLACE><PLACENAME>the Old Rectory</PLACENAME>, standing in more than twenty acres of gardens at <SETTLEMENT>Duntisbourne Rouse</SETTLEMENT>, a <REGION>Cotswold</REGION><GEOG/></PLACE> village which is quite out of the way although not far from <PLACE><SETTLEMENT>Cirencester</SETTL